  "prompt": "How do I buy a share of the Green Bay Packers' stock?",
  "response": "The Green Bay Packers are unique in professional sports ownership. Unlike most NFL teams, which are privately owned by individuals or ownership groups, the Packers are a publicly-owned, non-profit organization. This structure allows fans to purchase shares, but it's important to understand the specifics:\n\n### **Key Points About Packers Shares:**\n\n1. **Non-Traditional Stock:**\n   - **Non-Transferable:** Shares cannot be bought or sold on the open market. They are only sold directly by the Packers during official stock sales.\n   - **Limited Voting Rights:** Shareholders have limited voting rights, primarily related to team governance. However, control of the team remains with the Board of Directors and existing ownership structure.\n   - **No Dividends:** These shares don't function like typical corporate stocks. They don't pay dividends or appreciate in value based on the team's financial performance.\n\n2. **Stock Sales:**\n   - **Periodic and Limited:** The Packers typically hold stock sales infrequently (e.g., every few years) and distribute a limited number of shares.\n   - **Application Process:** Interested individuals must apply directly through the Packers' official channels during a stock sale period. There's often a lottery or selection process due to high demand.\n   - **Face Value:** Shares are sold at a nominal price (e.g., $100 per share) and come with a collectible certificate.\n\n3. **Current Availability:**\n   - As of my knowledge cutoff in April 2023, the Packers had announced stock sales scheduled for [provide specific dates if known]. However, schedules may change, so it's essential to verify the latest information.\n\n### **How to Purchase Packers Shares:**\n\n1. **Check Official Announcements:**\n   - Visit the [Green Bay Packers' official website](https://www.packers.com/) and navigate to the \"Stock\" section for updates on upcoming stock sales.\n\n2. **Sign Up for Notifications:**\n   - **Email Alerts:** Subscribe to Packers newsletters or alerts to receive notifications about stock sale events.\n   - **Social Media:** Follow the Packers on platforms like Twitter, Facebook, and Instagram for real-time updates.\n\n3. **Complete the Application:**\n   - During a stock sale period, you'll typically need to fill out an application form either online or by mail.\n   - Provide necessary personal information and payment details as required.\n\n4. **Wait for Confirmation:**\n   - Due to high demand, not all applicants may receive shares. Winners are usually selected through a random drawing.\n   - If selected, you'll receive your share certificates and information about shareholder benefits.\n\n### **Considerations:**\n\n- **Limited Financial Return:** Since Packers shares don't offer dividends or appreciate in value, they're primarily a way for fans to show support and engage with the team.\n- **Community Ownership:** Shareholders are part of a unique community ownership model that emphasizes the team's heritage and local support.\n- **Stay Informed:** Always use official Packers channels to get accurate information and avoid scams. Never provide personal or financial information to unofficial sources claiming to sell Packers shares.\n\n### **Conclusion:**\n\nPurchasing a share of the Green Bay Packers is a special opportunity reserved for dedicated fans who want to be part of the team's unique ownership structure. To buy shares, stay informed about upcoming stock sale events through the Packers' official communications and be prepared to apply promptly when sales open.\n\nFor the most current and detailed information, visit the [Green Bay Packers Stock Information page](https://www.packers.com/stock).",
